In the 1990s, a wooden board from the {{ill|Makimuku Ishizuka Kofun|ja|纒向石塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} was dated to 177 CE with dendrochronology. In 2001, other wood remains from the {{ill|Makimuku Katsuyama Kofun|ja|纒向勝山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} were dated between 103 and 199 CE. These findings imply construction dates around 180 CE for Makimuku Ishizuka and approximately 200 CE for Makimuku Katsuyama.<ref name=":03" />
== Dendrochronology == {| class="wikitable" !Dates CE !Ceramic types !Associated Kofun |- |158-188 |Makimuku 1 Shōnai 0 |Ishizuka |- |188-218 |Makimuku 2 Shōnai 1 |Katsuyama |- |218-243 |Makimuku 3 Shōnai 2/3 |Furu 0 |- |243-268 |Makimuku 4 Shōnai 3/5 |Furu 1 Hashihaka |}
