In the 1990s, a wooden board from the {{ill|Makimuku Ishizuka Kofun|ja|纒向石塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Makimuku Ishizuka Kofun|qq=}} was dated to 177 CE with dendrochronology. In 2001, other wood remains from the {{ill|Makimuku Katsuyama Kofun|ja|纒向勝山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Makimuku Katsuyama Kofun|qq=}} were dated between 103 and 199 CE. These findings imply construction dates around 180 CE for Makimuku Ishizuka and approximately 200 CE for Makimuku Katsuyama.<ref name=":03" />
